cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the order type of point sets in the unit square, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for determining the order type of a point set.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with the combinatorial structure of point sets and their order types.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the number of bits required to determine the order type of a point set.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses lower bounds on the number of bits required to determine the order type of a point set.
